    <h1>Why Most Published Research Findings Are False</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-6">John P. A. Ioannidis · 2005 · <a href="https://journals.plos.org/plosmedicine/article?id=10.1371/journal.pmed.0020124">PLoS Medicine 2(8): e124</a></p>

    <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-5 mb-8">
      <p class="text-lg" style="max-width:none">Most published research findings are false. The replication crisis, diagnosed before it had a name.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- The base rate problem SVG -->
    <h3>The base rate problem</h3>

    <p>Suppose one in ten hypotheses tested is actually true. A study with 80% power and a 5% significance threshold will produce results like this:</p>

    <div class="flex justify-center my-6">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 480 320" class="w-full max-w-md" style="font-family: ui-monospace, monospace;">
